{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":656,"text":"Well, I have a big announcement to make today,"},{"time":2959,"text":"and I'm really excited about this."},{"time":5132,"text":"And this may be a little bit of a surprise"},{"time":7460,"text":"to many of you who know my research"},{"time":10714,"text":"and what I've done well."},{"time":12869,"text":"I've really tried to solve some big problems:"},{"time":16273,"text":"counterterrorism, nuclear terrorism,"},{"time":18740,"text":"and health care and diagnosing and treating cancer,"},{"time":22388,"text":"but I started thinking about all these problems,"},{"time":24852,"text":"and I realized that the really biggest problem we face,"},{"time":29412,"text":"what all these other problems come down to,"},{"time":31660,"text":"is energy, is electricity, the flow of electrons."},{"time":35302,"text":"And I decided that I was going to set out"},{"time":38421,"text":"to try to solve this problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41803,"text":"And this probably is not what you're expecting."},{"time":45775,"text":"You're probably expecting me to come up here"},{"time":47427,"text":"and talk about fusion,"},{"time":49006,"text":"because that's what I've done most of my life."},{"time":50986,"text":"But this is actually a talk about, okay --"},{"time":54252,"text":"(Laughter) â€”"},{"time":56876,"text":"but this is actually a talk about fission."},{"time":59843,"text":"It's about perfecting something old,"},{"time":61369,"text":"and bringing something old into the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64019,"text":"Let's talk a little bit about how nuclear fission works."},{"time":68644,"text":"In a nuclear power plant, you have"},{"time":70388,"text":"a big pot of water that's under high pressure,"},{"time":73036,"text":"and you have some fuel rods,"},{"time":74554,"text":"and these fuel rods are encased in zirconium,"},{"time":76923,"text":"and they're little pellets of uranium dioxide fuel,"},{"time":79793,"text":"and a fission reaction is controlled and maintained at a proper level,"},{"time":83949,"text":"and that reaction heats up water,"},{"time":87100,"text":"the water turns to steam, steam turns the turbine,"},{"time":89925,"text":"and you produce electricity from it."},{"time":91855,"text":"This is the same way we've been producing electricity,"},{"time":94635,"text":"the steam turbine idea, for 100 years,"},{"time":98100,"text":"and nuclear was a really big advancement"},{"time":101121,"text":"in a way to heat the water,"},{"time":102701,"text":"but you still boil water and that turns to steam and turns the turbine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107156,"text":"And I thought, you know, is this the best way to do it?"},{"time":110972,"text":"Is fission kind of played out,"},{"time":113772,"text":"or is there something left to innovate here?"},{"time":116627,"text":"And I realized that I had hit upon something"},{"time":119212,"text":"that I think has this huge potential to change the world."},{"time":123516,"text":"And this is what it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127007,"text":"This is a small modular reactor."},{"time":129612,"text":"So it's not as big as the reactor you see in the diagram here."},{"time":134316,"text":"This is between 50 and 100 megawatts."},{"time":136719,"text":"But that's a ton of power."},{"time":138340,"text":"That's between, say at an average use,"},{"time":141789,"text":"that's maybe 25,000 to 100,000 homes could run off that."},{"time":146930,"text":"Now the really interesting thing about these reactors"},{"time":149508,"text":"is they're built in a factory."},{"time":151633,"text":"So they're modular reactors that are built"},{"time":153596,"text":"essentially on an assembly line,"},{"time":155941,"text":"and they're trucked anywhere in the world,"},{"time":158100,"text":"you plop them down, and they produce electricity."},{"time":160411,"text":"This region right here is the reactor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163853,"text":"And this is buried below ground, which is really important."},{"time":166164,"text":"For someone who's done a lot of counterterrorism work,"},{"time":168877,"text":"I can't extol to you"},{"time":171573,"text":"how great having something buried below the ground is"},{"time":174358,"text":"for proliferation and security concerns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178397,"text":"And inside this reactor is a molten salt,"},{"time":181910,"text":"so anybody who's a fan of thorium,"},{"time":184688,"text":"they're going to be really excited about this,"},{"time":186014,"text":"because these reactors happen to be really good"},{"time":191096,"text":"at breeding and burning the thorium fuel cycle,"},{"time":193680,"text":"uranium-233."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195731,"text":"But I'm not really concerned about the fuel."},{"time":198301,"text":"You can run these off -- they're really hungry,"},{"time":201525,"text":"they really like down-blended weapons pits,"},{"time":204957,"text":"so that's highly enriched uranium and weapons-grade plutonium"},{"time":207821,"text":"that's been down-blended."},{"time":208854,"text":"It's made into a grade where it's not usable for a nuclear weapon,"},{"time":212246,"text":"but they love this stuff."},{"time":215397,"text":"And we have a lot of it sitting around,"},{"time":217180,"text":"because this is a big problem."},{"time":218822,"text":"You know, in the Cold War, we built up this huge arsenal"},{"time":220939,"text":"of nuclear weapons, and that was great,"},{"time":223279,"text":"and we don't need them anymore,"},{"time":225734,"text":"and what are we doing with all the waste, essentially?"},{"time":229078,"text":"What are we doing with all the pits of those nuclear weapons?"},{"time":231493,"text":"Well, we're securing them, and it would be great"},{"time":233394,"text":"if we could burn them, eat them up,"},{"time":235138,"text":"and this reactor loves this stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237139,"text":"So it's a molten salt reactor. It has a core,"},{"time":240161,"text":"and it has a heat exchanger from the hot salt,"},{"time":243935,"text":"the radioactive salt, to a cold salt which isn't radioactive."},{"time":248005,"text":"It's still thermally hot but it's not radioactive."},{"time":250652,"text":"And then that's a heat exchanger"},{"time":252432,"text":"to what makes this design really, really interesting,"},{"time":255725,"text":"and that's a heat exchanger to a gas."},{"time":258733,"text":"So going back to what I was saying before about all power"},{"time":261277,"text":"being produced -- well, other than photovoltaic --"},{"time":264270,"text":"being produced by this boiling of steam and turning a turbine,"},{"time":268168,"text":"that's actually not that efficient, and in fact,"},{"time":270688,"text":"in a nuclear power plant like this,"},{"time":273064,"text":"it's only roughly 30 to 35 percent efficient."},{"time":277872,"text":"That's how much thermal energy the reactor's putting out"},{"time":280409,"text":"to how much electricity it's producing."},{"time":282062,"text":"And the reason the efficiencies are so low is these reactors"},{"time":284987,"text":"operate at pretty low temperature."},{"time":286693,"text":"They operate anywhere from, you know,"},{"time":288448,"text":"maybe 200 to 300 degrees Celsius."},{"time":292141,"text":"And these reactors run at 600 to 700 degrees Celsius,"},{"time":296140,"text":"which means the higher the temperature you go to,"},{"time":298845,"text":"thermodynamics tells you that you will have higher efficiencies."},{"time":301741,"text":"And this reactor doesn't use water. It uses gas,"},{"time":305415,"text":"so supercritical CO2 or helium,"},{"time":307893,"text":"and that goes into a turbine,"},{"time":309334,"text":"and this is called the Brayton cycle."},{"time":311195,"text":"This is the thermodynamic cycle that produces electricity,"},{"time":313669,"text":"and this makes this almost 50 percent efficient,"},{"time":316099,"text":"between 45 and 50 percent efficiency."},{"time":318989,"text":"And I'm really excited about this,"},{"time":320660,"text":"because it's a very compact core."},{"time":323173,"text":"Molten salt reactors are very compact by nature,"},{"time":327309,"text":"but what's also great is you get a lot more electricity out"},{"time":330614,"text":"for how much uranium you're fissioning,"},{"time":333359,"text":"not to mention the fact that these burn up."},{"time":335438,"text":"Their burn-up is much higher."},{"time":337030,"text":"So for a given amount of fuel you put in the reactor,"},{"time":339008,"text":"a lot more of it's being used."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341364,"text":"And the problem with a traditional nuclear power plant like this"},{"time":344549,"text":"is, you've got these rods that are clad in zirconium,"},{"time":348821,"text":"and inside them are uranium dioxide fuel pellets."},{"time":351550,"text":"Well, uranium dioxide's a ceramic,"},{"time":353724,"text":"and ceramic doesn't like releasing what's inside of it."},{"time":356940,"text":"So you have what's called the xenon pit,"},{"time":359241,"text":"and so some of these fission products love neutrons."},{"time":361345,"text":"They love the neutrons that are going on"},{"time":362592,"text":"and helping this reaction take place."},{"time":364992,"text":"And they eat them up, which means that, combined with"},{"time":367968,"text":"the fact that the cladding doesn't last very long,"},{"time":370205,"text":"you can only run one of these reactors"},{"time":371919,"text":"for roughly, say, 18 months without refueling it."},{"time":376447,"text":"So these reactors run for 30 years without refueling,"},{"time":381038,"text":"which is, in my opinion, very, very amazing,"},{"time":383758,"text":"because it means it's a sealed system."},{"time":385711,"text":"No refueling means you can seal them up"},{"time":388582,"text":"and they're not going to be a proliferation risk,"},{"time":391495,"text":"and they're not going to have"},{"time":393766,"text":"either nuclear material or radiological material"},{"time":396270,"text":"proliferated from their cores."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398582,"text":"But let's go back to safety, because everybody"},{"time":401646,"text":"after Fukushima had to reassess the safety of nuclear,"},{"time":405424,"text":"and one of the things when I set out to design a power reactor"},{"time":407974,"text":"was it had to be passively and intrinsically safe,"},{"time":411526,"text":"and I'm really excited about this reactor"},{"time":414005,"text":"for essentially two reasons."},{"time":416334,"text":"One, it doesn't operate at high pressure."},{"time":419278,"text":"So traditional reactors like a pressurized water reactor"},{"time":422519,"text":"or boiling water reactor, they're very, very hot water"},{"time":424951,"text":"at very high pressures, and this means, essentially,"},{"time":428358,"text":"in the event of an accident, if you had any kind of breach"},{"time":431222,"text":"of this stainless steel pressure vessel,"},{"time":434263,"text":"the coolant would leave the core."},{"time":436535,"text":"These reactors operate at essentially atmospheric pressure,"},{"time":439574,"text":"so there's no inclination for the fission products"},{"time":443480,"text":"to leave the reactor in the event of an accident."},{"time":446052,"text":"Also, they operate at high temperatures,"},{"time":448370,"text":"and the fuel is molten, so they can't melt down,"},{"time":451249,"text":"but in the event that the reactor ever went out of tolerances,"},{"time":455827,"text":"or you lost off-site power in the case"},{"time":458137,"text":"of something like Fukushima, there's a dump tank."},{"time":461327,"text":"Because your fuel is liquid, and it's combined with your coolant,"},{"time":465798,"text":"you could actually just drain the core"},{"time":468169,"text":"into what's called a sub-critical setting,"},{"time":470350,"text":"basically a tank underneath the reactor"},{"time":472304,"text":"that has some neutrons absorbers."},{"time":474264,"text":"And this is really important, because the reaction stops."},{"time":478054,"text":"In this kind of reactor, you can't do that."},{"time":480718,"text":"The fuel, like I said, is ceramic inside zirconium fuel rods,"},{"time":484199,"text":"and in the event of an accident in one of these type of reactors,"},{"time":487190,"text":"Fukushima and Three Mile Island --"},{"time":489327,"text":"looking back at Three Mile Island, we didn't really see this for a while â€”"},{"time":492222,"text":"but these zirconium claddings on these fuel rods,"},{"time":495708,"text":"what happens is, when they see high pressure water,"},{"time":498537,"text":"steam, in an oxidizing environment,"},{"time":501094,"text":"they'll actually produce hydrogen,"},{"time":503166,"text":"and that hydrogen has this explosive capability"},{"time":506094,"text":"to release fission products."},{"time":508304,"text":"So the core of this reactor, since it's not under pressure"},{"time":510518,"text":"and it doesn't have this chemical reactivity,"},{"time":512782,"text":"means that there's no inclination for the fission products"},{"time":516256,"text":"to leave this reactor."},{"time":517990,"text":"So even in the event of an accident,"},{"time":520255,"text":"yeah, the reactor may be toast, which is, you know,"},{"time":523973,"text":"sorry for the power company,"},{"time":525632,"text":"but we're not going to contaminate large quantities of land."},{"time":527732,"text":"So I really think that in the, say,"},{"time":531744,"text":"20 years it's going to take us to get fusion"},{"time":533872,"text":"and make fusion a reality,"},{"time":536092,"text":"this could be the source of energy"},{"time":538673,"text":"that provides carbon-free electricity."},{"time":541347,"text":"Carbon-free electricity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543005,"text":"And it's an amazing technology because"},{"time":546350,"text":"not only does it combat climate change,"},{"time":549180,"text":"but it's an innovation."},{"time":550684,"text":"It's a way to bring power to the developing world,"},{"time":553751,"text":"because it's produced in a factory and it's cheap."},{"time":556230,"text":"You can put them anywhere in the world you want to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558366,"text":"And maybe something else."},{"time":561622,"text":"As a kid, I was obsessed with space."},{"time":564143,"text":"Well, I was obsessed with nuclear science too, to a point,"},{"time":566886,"text":"but before that I was obsessed with space,"},{"time":569286,"text":"and I was really excited about, you know,"},{"time":571197,"text":"being an astronaut and designing rockets,"},{"time":573071,"text":"which was something that was always exciting to me."},{"time":575157,"text":"But I think I get to come back to this,"},{"time":578563,"text":"because imagine having a compact reactor in a rocket"},{"time":581864,"text":"that produces 50 to 100 megawatts."},{"time":584694,"text":"That is the rocket designer's dream."},{"time":587971,"text":"That's someone who is designing a habitat on another planet's dream."},{"time":591702,"text":"Not only do you have 50 to 100 megawatts"},{"time":593706,"text":"to power whatever you want to provide propulsion to get you there,"},{"time":598119,"text":"but you have power once you get there."},{"time":599518,"text":"You know, rocket designers who use solar panels"},{"time":603039,"text":"or fuel cells, I mean a few watts or kilowatts --"},{"time":605998,"text":"wow, that's a lot of power."},{"time":607591,"text":"I mean, now we're talking about 100 megawatts."},{"time":610036,"text":"That's a ton of power."},{"time":611209,"text":"That could power a Martian community."},{"time":613496,"text":"That could power a rocket there."},{"time":615093,"text":"And so I hope that"},{"time":617800,"text":"maybe I'll have an opportunity to kind of explore"},{"time":619921,"text":"my rocketry passion at the same time that I explore my nuclear passion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624588,"text":"And people say, \"Oh, well, you've launched this thing,"},{"time":627578,"text":"and it's radioactive, into space, and what about accidents?\""},{"time":630142,"text":"But we launch plutonium batteries all the time."},{"time":633175,"text":"Everybody was really excited about Curiosity,"},{"time":635294,"text":"and that had this big plutonium battery on board"},{"time":637895,"text":"that has plutonium-238,"},{"time":640014,"text":"which actually has a higher specific activity"},{"time":642414,"text":"than the low-enriched uranium fuel of these molten salt reactors,"},{"time":646158,"text":"which means that the effects would be negligible,"},{"time":649661,"text":"because you launch it cold,"},{"time":651113,"text":"and when it gets into space is where you actually activate this reactor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654824,"text":"So I'm really excited."},{"time":656132,"text":"I think that I've designed this reactor here"},{"time":658669,"text":"that can be an innovative source of energy,"},{"time":662574,"text":"provide power for all kinds of neat scientific applications,"},{"time":666255,"text":"and I'm really prepared to do this."},{"time":668783,"text":"I graduated high school in May, and --"},{"time":671550,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause) â€”"},{"time":675698,"text":"I graduated high school in May,"},{"time":677749,"text":"and I decided that I was going to start up a company"},{"time":680589,"text":"to commercialize these technologies that I've developed,"},{"time":682957,"text":"these revolutionary detectors for scanning cargo containers"},{"time":685814,"text":"and these systems to produce medical isotopes,"},{"time":688094,"text":"but I want to do this, and I've slowly been building up"},{"time":691542,"text":"a team of some of the most incredible people"},{"time":693795,"text":"I've ever had the chance to work with,"},{"time":695982,"text":"and I'm really prepared to make this a reality."},{"time":698744,"text":"And I think, I think, that looking at the technology,"},{"time":701841,"text":"this will be cheaper than or the same price as natural gas,"},{"time":707191,"text":"and you don't have to refuel it for 30 years,"},{"time":708991,"text":"which is an advantage for the developing world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711718,"text":"And I'll just say one more maybe philosophical thing"},{"time":714840,"text":"to end with, which is weird for a scientist."},{"time":716769,"text":"But I think there's something really poetic"},{"time":719263,"text":"about using nuclear power to propel us to the stars,"},{"time":723062,"text":"because the stars are giant fusion reactors."},{"time":725817,"text":"They're giant nuclear cauldrons in the sky."},{"time":728158,"text":"The energy that I'm able to talk to you today,"},{"time":731555,"text":"while it was converted to chemical energy in my food,"},{"time":733650,"text":"originally came from a nuclear reaction,"},{"time":736838,"text":"and so there's something poetic about, in my opinion,"},{"time":739614,"text":"perfecting nuclear fission"},{"time":742583,"text":"and using it as a future source of innovative energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746302,"text":"So thank you guys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748253,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}